00:00:00.840 --> 00:00:05.190
Maintaining some degree of website
accessibility is a legal requirement in

00:00:05.190 --> 00:00:08.125
many countries, including the UK and USA.

00:00:09.015 --> 00:00:13.754
But more than that, it's about creating
more inclusive online spaces for everyone.

00:00:16.994 --> 00:00:21.285
The website content accessibility
guidelines are designed to make content

00:00:21.285 --> 00:00:26.295
on desktops, laptops, tablets, and
mobile devices, more accessible to

00:00:26.295 --> 00:00:30.314
our wider range of people, especially
those with disabilities, including

00:00:30.314 --> 00:00:37.515
blindness and low vision, deafness
and hearing loss, limited movement.

00:00:39.195 --> 00:00:40.455
Speech disabilities,

00:00:42.915 --> 00:00:47.235
photo sensitivity, and some
learning disabilities like dyslexia.

00:00:47.985 --> 00:00:51.015
The guidelines state that
content and user interfaces

00:00:51.044 --> 00:00:55.694
should be perceivable, operable,
understandable, robust, and reliable.

00:00:56.114 --> 00:00:58.664
But what do these
principles mean in practice?

00:00:59.324 --> 00:01:03.074
Perceivable making your content
perceivable means improving

00:01:03.074 --> 00:01:04.754
visibility and readability.

00:01:06.270 --> 00:01:10.229
Through clear and consistent headers
that enhance the user experience,

00:01:10.530 --> 00:01:12.539
descriptive alt text for images

00:01:14.580 --> 00:01:16.679
and considerations for screen readers.

00:01:20.070 --> 00:01:20.610
Operable.

00:01:21.150 --> 00:01:25.979
An operable navigation and user interface
means users can navigate with a keyboard

00:01:26.039 --> 00:01:28.830
alone without using a mouse or track pad.

00:01:29.580 --> 00:01:31.965
They have time to read and
interact with your content.

00:01:32.700 --> 00:01:36.960
Understand their position on the page
and easily move through your website,

00:01:37.140 --> 00:01:39.090
finding all the info they're looking for.

00:01:41.790 --> 00:01:42.720
Understandable.

00:01:43.320 --> 00:01:47.520
It's important to make your content and
the user journey as easy as possible

00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:52.260
to understand, use clear and simple
language, be consistent throughout

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:57.420
the navigation, and provide meaningful
error messages to minimize confusion.

00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:01.470
Robust and reliable.

00:02:01.679 --> 00:02:05.760
When building robust and reliable
websites, it's important to ensure

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:09.960
compatibility with various browsers
and assistive technologies, allowing

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:13.650
users to access your content
regardless of the tools they use.

00:02:14.055 --> 00:02:18.135
This means both future proofing and
iterating for the latest technology.

00:02:18.765 --> 00:02:23.114
Once you understand these principles, you
can start to implement them by following

00:02:23.114 --> 00:02:27.165
the website content accessibility
guidelines linked in the description.

00:02:27.644 --> 00:02:34.065
Then you can assess how well your
site conforms a basic accessibility,

00:02:37.065 --> 00:02:38.535
AA strong accessibility.

00:02:40.725 --> 00:02:42.795
AAA, excellent accessibility.

00:02:44.535 --> 00:02:47.265
AA is the standard all
websites should be aiming for.

00:02:47.805 --> 00:02:51.435
While AAA criteria are generally
considered more applicable to

00:02:51.435 --> 00:02:56.145
specific circumstances and content
types, it's unlikely you'll need to

00:02:56.145 --> 00:03:00.825
tick every AAA box, but some may be
relevant to your business or users.

00:03:01.484 --> 00:03:06.135
So next time you start a website project
or update your site, be sure to check

00:03:06.135 --> 00:03:10.454
whether it meets user expectations
and accessibility guidelines or get

00:03:10.454 --> 00:03:12.345
in touch and we'll be happy to help.

